> Problem Statement

You are given an integer array nums sorted in non-decreasing order.

Your task is to:

Remove the duplicates in-place such that each unique element appears only once.

Maintain the relative order of the elements.

Let the number of unique elements be k.

> Requirements:

Modify the input array nums in-place.

The first k elements of nums should contain the unique elements in order.

The elements beyond index k - 1 can be ignored.

Return the value of k.


> # Solution code:


class Solution:
    def removeDuplicates(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:
        if not nums:
            return 0
        
        i = 1  # position for next unique element

        for j in range(1, len(nums)):
            if nums[j] != nums[i - 1]:
                nums[i] = nums[j]
                i += 1
        
        return i
